refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
GdImagefalseimagecrop GdImageimage arrayrectangle
Crops an image to the given rectangular area and returns the resulting image. The given image is not modified.

&reftitle.parameters;

 &gd.image.description;

  rectangle



    The cropping rectangle as array with keys
    x, y, width and
    height.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;



   &gd.changelog.image-param;


    8.0.0

     On success, this function returns a GDImage instance now;
     previously, a resource was returned.

  &reftitle.examples;

   imagecrop example


     This example shows how to crop an image to a square area.



<?php
$im = imagecreatefrompng('example.png');
$size = min(imagesx($im), imagesy($im));
$im2 = imagecrop($im, ['x' => 0, 'y' => 0, 'width' => $size, 'height' => $size]);
if ($im2 !== FALSE) {
    imagepng($im2, 'example-cropped.png');
    imagedestroy($im2);
}
imagedestroy($im);
?>
